    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:hi <A> <B>` just fails to parse with:\n\n```\nE416: Missing equal sign: <B>\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:hi <A> <B>` is the same as running:\n\n`:hi DiffsAdd DiffsDelete`\n\nThis idea just came to mind, especially as it doesn't seem impossible to parse.\n\nFeel free to close if this is an unecessary divergence from vim behavior - but I'd just like to know explicitly why.\n\nHappy to work on this.",
