        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Indeed, I didn't get your proposition. :-)  After your reply - now it's clear what you want.\n\nI don't think that `hi x x` should be able to loop over multiple groups to display multiple lines with their configuration. Imagine the costs of parsing the func parameters and determinate if it's a group or a configuration. \n\nI think it's more intuitive that without parameters it's an `print/get` of the group, and with parameters it's an `set` Otherwise an leading parameter, after `hi` would make sense.\nBut that's only my point of view as a regular vim user.\n\nYes, this sould be evaluated by the vim/nvim core team.\n\nI replied to you in the first place because I thought you need help while struggling with the `hi link`. :-)\n ",
